  "prompt": "My car back glass has been broken, how can I claim United India insurance?",
  "response": "To claim insurance for your broken car back glass with United India Insurance, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Review Your Policy:** Check your insurance policy documents to understand the coverage related to glass damage. Ensure that you're covered for glass breakage.\n\n2. **Inform the Insurance Company:** Contact United India Insurance through their customer service hotline or visit the nearest branch. Provide them with the necessary details such as your policy number, the nature of the damage, and the circumstances under which it occurred.\n\n3. **File a Claim:** Request a claim form from the insurance company. Fill it out accurately with all required information. Include details like date, time, and place of the incident, along with a description of how the damage occurred.\n\n4. **Documentation:** Gather all necessary documents to support your claim. This may include:\n   - Copy of your insurance policy\n   - Aadhar card or identity proof\n   - Driving license\n   - FIR (if applicable)\n   - Photographs of the damaged glass\n   - Any other relevant documents\n\n5. **Submit the Claim:** Submit the completed claim form along with all required documents to the insurance company. Make sure to keep copies for your records.\n\n6. **Inspection (if required):** An insurance adjuster may need to inspect the damage. Be prepared to take your vehicle to a designated garage for assessment if asked.\n\n7. **Claim Approval:** Once the claim is processed, you will receive intimation about the approval status. If approved, the cost of replacing the back glass will be settled according to the terms of your policy.\n\n8. **Repairs:** After the claim is approved, get the back glass replaced. You may need to use an authorized service center, so check if your policy specifies this.\n\n9. **Follow Up:** Keep in touch with the insurance company for updates on your claim status if there are any delays.\n\nAlways refer to your specific policy documents for the most accurate and relevant information regarding your coverage and claims process.",
